The paper deals with algorithmic aspects of a domination problem in graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The paper discusses the problem in the context of various graph classes such as planar graphs, doubly chordal graphs, and bipartite graphs. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
